<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<link rel="icon" href="favicon.ico" sizes="any">
<title>Irodori — What To Do</title>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>

<section id="quiz">
  <h1>Irodori—What can you do?</h1>
  <p class="intro">
        <a href="https://www.irodori.jpf.go.jp/en/index.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Irodori</a>
        is the Japan Foundation's free, wonderfully down-to-earth course for actually
        living life in Japan. Great stuff, but if you've already got some Japanese
        under your belt, trudging from lesson one is nobody's idea of a good time.
  </p>
  <p class="intro">
        Have a skim through each <strong>skill</strong> (the book talks about "can-do's") and
        <strong>sentence pattern</strong>: got it, a bit rusty, or totally new? At
        the end you'll get a tidy little cheat-sheet of what to
        <strong>skip</strong>, what to <strong>review</strong>, and what's worth
        actually sitting down to <strong>study</strong>.
  </p>
  <p class="intro">
        If at any point you feel like you don't really know any of the question, you can just stop and <button type="button" class="small js-see-results">See results &rarr;</button>!
  </p>
  <hr>
  <p class="intro small">
        All the information was compiled from the <a href="https://www.irodori.jpf.go.jp/en/resources.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">resources</a> the creators of Irodori put together, only restructured to fit this questionairre.
        AI was used to translate and provide descriptions and examples, by strictly following my <a href="https://github.com/snorthman/IrodoriWhatToDo/blob/main/SPEC.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener">specifications</a>.
        Feel free to check out the <a href="https://github.com/snorthman/IrodoriWhatToDo" target="_blank" rel="noopener">code repository</a>.
  </p>
  <p class="intro small" id="clear-row" hidden>
      <button type="button" class="small muted js-clear">Clear your answers</button>
  </p>
  <form id="answers">
    {% for lesson in lessons %}
        {% if lesson.skill %}
        <div class="q q-skill" style="--accent: {{ lesson.book.color }}">
          <div class="q-num"></div>
          <div class="q-body">
            <div class="q-head"><strong>Skill</strong> Can-do</div>
            <div class="question">{{ lesson.skill.question }}</div>
            <div class="example-label">Example:</div>
            <div class="examples">
              <div class="example-box">{{ lesson.skill.example }}</div>
              <div class="example-box">{{ lesson.skill.example_translated }}</div>
            </div>
            <div class="opts">
              <label><input type="radio" name="skill-{{ lesson.index }}" value="can-do">Can do</label>
              <label><input type="radio" name="skill-{{ lesson.index }}" value="needs-revision">Needs practice</label>
              <label><input type="radio" name="skill-{{ lesson.index }}" value="new">New to me</label>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="q-side">
{#            <span class="situation">{{ lesson.skill.situation.label }}</span>#}
            <span class="q-type">{{ lesson.skill.type.value }}</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        {% endif %}
        {% if lesson.sentence %}
        <div class="q q-sentence" style="--accent: {{ lesson.book.color }}">
          <div class="q-num"></div>
          <div class="q-body">
            <div class="q-head"><strong>Sentence</strong> Pattern Can-do</div>
            <div class="question">{{ lesson.sentence.pattern_translated }}</div>
            <div class="example-label">Example:</div>
            <div class="examples">
              <div class="example-box">{{ lesson.sentence.example|safe }}</div>
              <div class="example-box">{{ lesson.sentence.example_translated }}</div>
            </div>
            <div class="opts">
              <label><input type="radio" name="sentence-{{ lesson.index }}" value="can-do">Can do</label>
              <label><input type="radio" name="sentence-{{ lesson.index }}" value="needs-revision">Needs revision</label>
              <label><input type="radio" name="sentence-{{ lesson.index }}" value="new">New to me</label>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        {% endif %}
    {% endfor %}
  </form>
  <div class="sticky-bar">
    <div class="progress"><span id="progress-fill"></span></div>
    <p id="progress-text" class="progress-text"></p>
    <button type="button" class="js-see-results">See results &rarr;</button>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="results" hidden>
  <h1>Your Irodori study plan</h1>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Book</th><th>Lesson</th><th>Skill</th><th>Sentence</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody></tbody>
  </table>
  <div class="sticky-bar">
    <button type="button" id="back">&larr; Back to Can-do's</button>
    <button type="button" class="js-print">Print / Save as PDF</button>
  </div>
</section>

<footer class="site-footer">
  <p>Built by <span class="author">snorthman</span>.</p>
  <p>Not affiliated with <em>Irodori: Japanese for Life in Japan</em> or its creators.</p>
  <p>All rights to the original course materials belong to the Japan Foundation Japanese-Language Institute, Urawa.</p>
</footer>

<script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
